 According to Capt. Khanyisile Zwane, Middelburg police spokesperson, Patricia Shabangu (35) sustained serious burn wounds when battery acid was allegedly thrown on to her face by her boyfriend. The incident occurred on Sunday at 01:30 at the Uitkyk informal settlement. Ms Shabangu was transported to the Middelburg Hospital and later transferred to the Witbank Hospital, where she later succumbed to her wounds. She had burn wounds on her face and neck. It is suspected that she swallowed some of the battery acid, causing irreparable damage to her intestines. An initial attempted murder docket has now been changed to one of murder. No one was arrested at the time of going to press.    Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za